India 117-2 to Trail England by 104 Runs in Second Cricket Test

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-07-30T12:36:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-30/india-117-2-to-trail-england-by-104-runs-in-second-cricket-test.html
India  reached 117-2 at lunch to
trail England by 104 runs on day three of the second cricket
Test at Trent Bridge in Nottingham.  Rahul David is 44 not out and Sachin Tendulkar, bidding to
become the first player with 100 international centuries, has
14. VVS Laxman scored 54 before being caught by wicketkeeper
Matt Prior from  Tim Bresnan .  England won the opening Test by 196 runs. It can overtake
India at the top of the International Cricket Council rankings
by winning the four-game series by two Tests or more.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  